² Ipse cum leyatis circumita] In the Roman camp watches were kept at each of the four gates, and these were relieved every three hours; so that there were four sets in the night. And, to keep the men on the watch strictly to their duty, there was a circuitio vigilum, or a visiting of the watch, performed four times every night. This, for a long time, was the business of the Tribunes ; at length they were allowed ω execute this pieoe of their office by deputies 3 and at last, a set of men were appointed for the purpose, called circuitores.
